# UDS Factory Docs Currency

The docs site explains the Component Factory in plain English on the
**Factory tab** of the Cursor Workflows page
([`uds-docs/app/(site)/cursor-workflows/CursorWorkflowsClient.tsx`](../../uds-docs/app/(site)/cursor-workflows/CursorWorkflowsClient.tsx)).
That tab is the non-developer's "how the factory works" — lifecycle, the
four phases, the quality gates, the tag model, what it won't do. This
rule keeps it honest when the factory itself changes.

## When you MUST update the Factory tab

If a change to the factory skillset —
[`generate-uds-figma-component/SKILL.md`](../skills/generate-uds-figma-component/SKILL.md),
[`uds-figma-factory-quality.mdc`](./uds-figma-factory-quality.mdc), or
[`uds-figma-plugin-api-gotchas.mdc`](./uds-figma-plugin-api-gotchas.mdc)
— changes something a **designer would notice**, update the Factory tab
in the same change. That includes:

- a new or changed phase (A / B / C / D) or what the designer does at it
- a new or changed quality gate the "Why you can trust the draft"
  section summarizes
- a changed lifecycle step (how drafts are accepted, how the docs site
  catches up, the page-naming / tag behavior)
- a changed trigger prompt or a change to "What it won't do"

Then add a `SITE_CHANGELOG` entry per
[`uds-site-changelog.mdc`](./uds-site-changelog.mdc), in designer voice
per [`communication-style.mdc`](./communication-style.mdc) — the tab is
rendered page copy for humans, not an implementation log.

## When you DON'T

Internal-only edits that leave what the factory produces (and how a
designer interacts with it) unchanged — prose clarifications, wording,
examples, `lastUpdated`-only bumps — do NOT require a Factory-tab
update. The bar is "would a designer reading the tab notice this is now
wrong or incomplete?"

## Accuracy is a human check

[`scripts/audit-agent-docs-currency.sh`](../../scripts/audit-agent-docs-currency.sh)
verifies the page *references* the factory files (and this rule), so a
renamed or deleted file can't silently strand the docs. It CANNOT verify
the prose is *accurate* — an audit can't read intent. After any
user-facing factory change, re-read the Factory tab and confirm it still
matches reality. That judgment is the editor's, not the audit's.

## Editing this rule

This file lives under `.cursor/rules/`, so
[`uds-rule-discipline.mdc`](./uds-rule-discipline.mdc) applies: bump
`lastUpdated:` and run `bash scripts/regenerate-toolchain.sh` when you
edit it, and keep its card on the Cursor Workflows Rules tab.

